===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|i}} – based on the structure of {{zh-l|*言}}, with an additional short horizontal stroke inside the {{zh-l|*口|mouth}}, forming a shape similar to {{zh-l|*甘}}. The ''{{w|Shuowen Jiezi}}'' describes the structure as {{lang|zh|从言含一}} ("from {{zh-l|*言}} containing {{zh-l|*一}}").

The added stroke graphically seals the mouth, likely representing partially closed or muffled vocalization, in contrast with {{zh-l|*言|articulate speech}}. This is consistent with the ''*ʔəm'' word family, which clusters around meanings of covering and closure: compare homophones {{zh-l|*瘖|tr=*ʔum}} and {{zh-l|*喑||mute|tr=*ʔəmʔ}}, and {{zh-l|*韽||faint, weak sound|tr=*ʔˤəm}}.

See also {{zh-l|*言}}.

