===Etymology 4===
{{etymid|ja|ne}}
{{ja-kanjitab|ね|yomi=k|alt=哭}}
{{IPAfont|⟨ne<sub>2</sub>⟩}} → *{{IPAchar|/nəɨ/}} → {{IPAchar|/ne/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=ね|-}}.  First attested in the ''{{w|Kojiki}}'' of 712, with the phonetic spelling {{m|ja|泥}}.<ref name="KDJc">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten Concise}}</ref>

The original meaning appears to have been "a sound or cry, as made by an insect, bird, or beast".<ref name="KDJc"/>  The verb for making such a sound is {{m|ja|鳴く|tr=naku||to make a sound; to cry out}}, cognate with {{m|ja|泣く|tr=naku||to cry, to weep}}.  It remains unclear if this noun ''ne'' ("sound") might be related to the verb ''naku'' ("to make a sound").

